Coming from #13742, @andrewwillowen demonstrated a perhaps more severe instance of this (I minimized it slightly):

```py
import pytest

@pytest.mark.parametrize("n", iter(range(1)))
class Test:
    def test_1(self, n):
        pass

    def test_2(self, n):
        pass
```

I'm reopening the issue since the behavior on the above is quite perilous, it skips `test_2`. I think we should try to improve this if possible.
